    "explanation": "We place the code for which we wish to catch exceptions inside curly brackets with a try at the front. At the end, we put catch(...). This then catches exceptions of all types. Here are some possible related questions: e@ What is exception safety? e How do you rethrow an object?\n\n7. CODING IN C++ e If I catch an object of type X and throw an object of type Y under what circumstances is Y caught by the catch? C)",
