    "explanation": "This is a trick question. The obvious answer of averaging the speeds is incorrect. Instead, we compute the times needed. Two laps means 2 miles. To travel 2 miles at 60 mph takes 2 minutes. To travel 1 mile at 30 mph also takes 2 minutes. We therefore have no time left to go round the second time. The car would have to travel infinitely fast.\n\n8. LOGIC/BRAINTEASERS Here are some possible related questions: e If the car has a top speed of 120 mph, what's the fastest average speed that can be attained? e Why doesn't averaging the speeds work? O",
